---

# 14. Authentication

Every request SHALL be authenticated.

Authentication mechanisms are implementation-specific.

Authorization SHALL be policy-based.

---

# 15. Error Responses

Every response SHALL contain:

* code
* message
* correlation_id

Internal stack traces SHALL NEVER be returned.

---

# 16. Versioning

The API SHALL be versioned.

Example:

```text id="api12"
/api/v1/...
```

Breaking changes require a new API version.

---

# 17. Design Invariants

Invariant 1

Every endpoint maps to one Command.

---

Invariant 2

The API never exposes internal services.

---

Invariant 3

The API remains transport-independent.

REST is the reference implementation.
